history.content: When you try to enroll in 2 classes that are conflicting, SIS will prompt you to fill out a request form to enroll in overlapping courses. You'll need to explain why you're requesting to do this. Let us know if you don't get the form; SIS has been making some changes lately.

I know that at least one (probably both) of these Computer Science classes are webcast and attendance isn't mandatory. Will the new SIS let me enroll in both if the lecture time conflicts? Is there any way I can get around this?
